Meanwhile, Nina from Bradford is addicted to eating novels, Rebecca from Herefordshire eats her own hair and six-year-old Charlotte is starring to eat carpets and toys. programme.desc: A teenage boy raised by gorillas in Africa falls for a pretty conservationist following a chance meeting in the jungle, but finds their romance threatened by a menacing Silverback, and a scheming capitalist in search of a new energy source in this animated adaptation of Edgar Rice Burroughs' classic tale. John Greystoke, Jr. was just a toddler when he accompanied his adventurous mother and father on a journey into Africa in search of a mineral that could revolutionize the energy industry. That trip turns tragic, however, when their helicopter crashes in a race to escape a massive storm, leaving young John the sole survivor. Raised from that day forward by a motherly gorilla named Kala, the boy, now named Tarzan, quickly integrates into the family of primates. But alpha male Silverback Tablat refuses to accept Tarzan's presence, viewing him as a direct threat to the clan. Nearly a decade later, Tarzan encounters beautiful Jane Porter, and begins to long for human contact. When Jane returns to the jungle accompanied by smooth-talking entrepreneur William Clayton a few years later, her relationship with Tarzan is rekindled. But while Clayton has ostensibly come to the jungle to support Jane's conservationist endeavors, he's actually searching for the very same energy source once sought by Tarzan's father, and hopes to turn a tidy profit by exploiting the precious resource. The situation turns critical when Jane recognizes Clayton's true intentions, and the only one who can save her from both the villainous industrialist and the menacing Tablat is the noble Tarzan of the apes(n)

programme.desc: Jules Hudson helps a couple looking for a property in rural Cheshire, and also visits the Anderson Boat Lift, which links the River Weaver and the Trent and Mersey Canal.(n)

programme.title: Wreck-It Ralph
programme.desc: A video game villain grows tired of always being the bad guy, and ventures into other games in search of the chance to be a hero, unwittingly causing chaos in the process. When a deadly threat to the entire arcade appears, it falls to him to set things right. Animated adventure, with the voices of John C Reilly, Sarah Silverman and Jane Lynch.(n)

programme.title: Monsters University
programme.desc: Student creatures Mike and Sulley attend university to learn how to be scary, but their rivalry gets them both kicked off the course. The monstrous duo must learn how to work together if they are to realise their dreams of terrifying children. Animated comedy prequel, with the voices of John Goodman, Billy Crystal and Helen Mirren.(n)

programme.title: Pointless Celebrities
programme.desc: Alexander Armstrong and Richard Osman invite figures from the world of musical theatre to take part in the unorthodox general knowledge quiz, in which contestants must guess the least likely correct answers given to questions posed to members of the public. Lyricists Tim Rice and Don Black join forces, while How Do You Solve a Problem Like Maria winner Connie Fisher teams up with her former rival Siobhan Dillon. Former Chicago star Claire Sweeney pairs with comedy actor and one-time Wicked star Nigel Planer, and Cory English, the American actor who recently starred in a UK tour of The producers, collaborates with comedian and Spamalot star Phill Jupitus.(n)

programme.title: Doctor Who
programme.desc: Hidden within the Haereticum, the secret library of blasphemy deep in the heart of the Vatican, there lies an ancient book. Known only as The Veritas, anyone who reads the contents of this book is found dead. Now, a new translation of The Veritas has managed to find its way online, putting millions in danger. As the viral tome spreads across the web, the Vatican appeals to the Doctor for help, but to truly understand the nature of the problem, he must first read The Veritas himself. Can he survive the ultimate truth? Sci-fi adventure, starring Peter Capaldi, Pearl Mackie and Matt Lucas.(n)

programme.title: Who Dares Wins
programme.desc: Nick Knowles challenges two pairs of complete strangers to team up, with pair each battling to outdo the other by listing as much as they know about a given subject. The first couple to win two rounds get to play for £50,000 and each time the champions defeat a new set of opponents their winnings mount up.(n)

programme.title: Casualty
programme.desc: Now that Grace is living with Sam, Connie and Hugo have become a contented family unit of their own. However, when Hugo's father Jim gets in touch, and tells Connie he is planning to take Hugo back, the troubled youngster runs away. Determined to keep him from harm, Connie, Jim, Jacob and Phil, a policeman receiving treatment in the ED, mount a search. Meanwhile, Lily returns to work to get closer to Iain, but proves she is still not quite at the top of her game when she fails to notice a patient rescued from the ruins of a collapsed building has tell-tale track-marks on her arm.(n)

programme.title: Clique
programme.desc: New series. Holly and Georgia have been best friends since the age of 11, so when it came time for them to leave home and head to university, it was obvious they should apply to the same academy. As the pair enjoy their first couple of weeks of freedom, they find themselves drawn to an elite clique of alpha girls, led by lecturer Jude McDermid. Drama, starring Synnove Karlsen.(n)

programme.title: Clique
programme.desc: Recent events leave Holly reeling, as she grows increasingly suspicious of Solasta Finance. When Georgia finds out she has been accepted onto the internship, she also announces that she will be moving into the clique girls' house. As Holly finds herself increasingly isolated, banker Rory seems to take an interest in her, and through him she may have found a way into the heart of Alistair McDermid's glittering world. Drama, starring Synnove Karlsen.(n)

programme.title: Insomnia
programme.desc: A detective is sent to Alaska to investigate a murder during a month when the sun does not set. Sleep deprivation starts to take its toll, and he accidentally shoots his partner dead. He tries to cover it up, but the criminal they were hunting has seen everything and blackmails the cop into helping him escape justice. Thriller directed by Christopher Nolan, starring Al Pacino, Robin Williams and Hilary Swank.(n)

programme.title: Breakfast
programme.desc: A round-up of national and international news, plus sports reports, weather forecasts and arts and entertainment features.(n)

programme.title: The Andrew Marr Show
programme.desc: A round-up of the week's stories, featuring interviews with key figures in politics and current affairs, and a look at the Sunday papers. Including news and weather at 9.00.(n)

programme.title: The Big Questions
programme.desc: Nicky Campbell presents moral and religious discussions from Oasis Academy MediaCityUK, Salford.(n)

programme.title: Sunday Politics London
programme.desc: The week's events at Westminster, presented by Andrew Neil. Including news and a regional round-up.(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Charlie Ross takes over the presenting duties at the Westpoint antiques and collectors fair in Devon. Experts Kate Bliss and Colin Young help two teams of married couples pick up bargains, and Charlie reveals a past purchase that he regrets ever making.(n)

programme.title: Money for Nothing
programme.desc: Sarah Moore and the team transform items from a recycling centre in Witley, Surrey, including a cuckoo clock, a pair of bamboo chairs and an old kitchen unit. Arthur Smith narrates.(n)

programme.title: Escape to the Country
programme.desc: Two campervan enthusiasts with a budget of £400,000 seek a home near the Peak District, and Nicki Chapman tries her hand at woodcraft with Britain's last traditional bowl turner.(n)

programme.title: Shop Well for Less
programme.desc: Alex Jones and Steph McGovern help the Parmar family from North London, who are addicted to brand labels, and try to convince them that cheaper alternatives can be just as good by giving their house a new look and organising a pop-up shop of their belongings. Plus, Professor Avi Shankar reveals how companies use packaging to catch the customers' eye, as five travel mugs are put through their paces to see which one comes out on top, and Alex gets the Parmar's to blind test three stand mixers to see if price really does equal quality.(n)

programme.title: Lifeline
programme.desc: Gabby Logan presents an appeal on behalf of Tiny Tickers, a charity working to increase the detection rate of heart disease in children, including before birth.(n)

programme.title: Points of View
programme.desc: Jeremy Vine presents a selection of viewers' comments on BBC shows, a chance to see memorable clips, and an insight into what goes on behind the scenes of new programmes.(n)

programme.title: Songs of Praise
programme.desc: Josie d'Arby meets nuns at a convent in Pembrokeshire, and Church detective Richard Taylor explores the history of Baptists in the UK.(n)

programme.title: RHS Chelsea Flower Show 2017
programme.desc: New series. Sophie Raworth and Joe Swift present a sneak preview of the Royal Horticultural Society's prestigious annual event 24 hours ahead of the showground officially opening to the public. They showcase some of the most spectacular gardens and exhibits that will be featured in this year's show and go behind the scenes with the RHS staff as the event is prepared, revealing the huge amount of work that goes into getting everything ready, with just three weeks from initial set-up to the first visitors arriving.(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Matt Baker explores the rise and fall of the orchards in the Clyde Valley. Ellie Harrison explores some of Scotland's oldest forests and meets an urban beekeeper, and Sean Fletcher visits a traditional mill using machinery that is centuries old. Adam Henson and Charlotte Smith visit an agricultural project in Newport Pagnell and Tom Heap reports on the problem of microplastics in the ocean.(n)

programme.title: Antiques Roadshow
programme.desc: Fiona Bruce presents a second show from Ightham Mote near Sevenoaks, where finds include a gold ring containing a lock of Lord Byron's hair, a collection of postcards from 1916 that reveal how a British PoW sent messages to his family, and a pair of Chinese paintings that make a big impression on specialist David Battie.(n)

programme.title: Inspector George Gently
programme.desc: The first of two final cases for the detective, played by Martin Shaw. Gently is on the brink of retirement when he, Bacchus and Coles re-open the case of a woman convicted of killing her husband, hoping to uncover a long-buried miscarriage of justice. However, the investigation places Gently's career on the line and stirs up tension with Bacchus, who worked on the original investigation.(n)

programme.title: Match of the Day
programme.desc: Gary Lineker present is joined by Alan Shearer and Frank Lampard to present highlights of the final day of the Premier League season, with matches including Hull City v Tottenham Hotspur at the KCOM Stadium and Swansea City v West Bromwich Albion at the Liberty Stadium. Issues at the top and bottom of the table are depend on the concluding set of fixtures, with the race for the top four and to avoid relegation having been tense all season.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: The Charge of the Light Brigade
programme.desc: A British major and his brother stationed in India during the Crimean War become rivals when they fall in love with the same woman. An allied local ruler betrays the British, carrying out a massacre of civilians and prompting the major to swear revenge on him - ultimately leading a suicidal attack on an enemy artillery position. Fact-based drama, starring Errol Flynn, Olivia de Havilland and Nigel Bruce.(n)

programme.title: Kismet
programme.desc: A penniless poet in ancient Baghdad finds his life on the line after a case of mistaken identity. It proves to be only the first in a series of strange twists of fate, but he uses his cunning to stay ahead of his enemies and rise to a position of power. Musical fantasy, starring Howard Keel and Ann Blyth. Featuring songs based on music by Borodin, including Stranger in Paradise and Baubles, Bangles and Beads.(n)

programme.title: Homes Under the Hammer
programme.desc: Lucy Alexander visits a centuries old building in Castle Donington in Leicestershire, while Dion Dublin looks round a complex auction lot of two houses and a piece of land in Silverdale near Newcastle under Lyme. Martin Roberts also meets two young property developers hoping to convert former council offices in Tredegar, Wales.(n)

programme.title: Monty Halls' Great Hebridean Escape
programme.desc: The volunteer wildlife ranger hatches a plan to raise money to restore abandoned walking trails by hosting a feast showcasing local produce at Niall Leveson-Gower's hotel. He hopes to take guests on a culinary journey by preparing food from the sea, shore, land and farmers' produce including salmon, clams and venison. He also enjoys the rare sightings of sea eagles teaching their young to fly, and a beached whale.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The first of the North West region heats sees Tom Parker, Paul Askew and Ellis Barrie prepare their starters for the banquet marking 140 years of the Wimbledon tennis championships. The dishes include a salad made up of 10 complex elements, and a cucumber and oyster creation, with a Great British Menu veteran judging their efforts.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: North West chefs Paul Askew, Ellis Barrie and Tom Parker produce fish-based dishes, with Ellis aiming to create the flavour of a summer barbecue without actually using one. Tom serves oysters and langoustines with a risky champagne sauce that combines both traditional British and Asian flavours, while Paul cooks turbot and oysters.(n)

programme.title: Talking Pictures
programme.desc: Exploring the relationship between director Alfred Hitchcock and his stars, featuring interviews with the man himself, Kim Novak, Tippi Hedren, Joan Fontaine, Janet Leigh and Sean Connery. Sylvia Syms narrates.(n)

programme.title: North By Northwest
programme.desc: A suave advertising executive is mistaken for an American intelligence agent by a foreign spy and finds himself drawn into a world of espionage and adventure, leading to a high-tension cross-country chase made more perilous when the FBI intervenes. Alfred Hitchcock's thriller, starring Cary Grant, James Mason, Eva Marie Saint, Leo G Carroll and Martin Landau.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Philip Serrell and Charles Hanson appraise a chair made from the wood of Lord Nelson's ship while visiting the National Maritime Museum in Falmouth, Cornwall.(n)

programme.title: Trust Me, I'm a Vet
programme.desc: In the final episode, Judy Puddifoot investigates the warning signs dogs give out before becoming aggressive, and Steve Leonard looks into the latest research that suggests feeding your cat only fish-based pet foods over the long term could lead to health problems. Elsewhere, Alice Rhodes discovers that one in five cats in the UK lives in a state of long-term anxiety because they share a house with another cat, and she runs a series of unique experiments to test different stress-reducing methods. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Gardeners' World
programme.desc: Mark Lane is in Hackney, finding out how a car wrecker's yard at the side of a Tudor National Trust property has been transformed into an award-winning garden used by the local community. Carol Klein visits Oxford Botanic garden to view their euphorbia collection and Rachel de Thame visits a garden which has opened to the public every year for 90 years as part of the National Gardens Scheme. Including Weather.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: Exploring efforts by conservationists and scientists to protect wildlife including turtles, dolphins and monk seals in Hawaii's surf zone, as its marine animals face a growing threat from washed-up plastic. This comes on top of creatures having to cope with an increasing number of visitors to beaches. With a contribution by Hawaii-born musician Jack Johnson.(n)

programme.title: Mexico: Earth's Festival of Life
programme.desc: Exploring the forests of the Yucatan Peninsula, which contain the ruins of the Mayan civilisation and a wide range of wildlife, including jaguars, monkeys and tropical birds. The region also holds a secret that is the key to how Mexico's people and animals are able to survive during the country's dry season.(n)

programme.title: Yorkshire Wolds Way
programme.sub-title: Yorkshire Wolds Way with Paul Rose.
programme.desc: Part two of two. Adventurer Paul Rose concludes his exploration of the 79-mile Yorkshire Wolds Way, taking to the skies to get a unique view of its stretch of chalk downland. He also receives a special invitation to a military base that has been keeping the nation safe since the start of the Second World War.(n)

programme.title: Dad's Army
programme.desc: Captain Mainwaring organises a dance in an attempt to boost platoon morale - but Pike interrupts proceedings to make an important announcement regarding his girlfriend Violet. Classic comedy by Jimmy Perry and David Croft, starring Ian Lavender. First broadcast in 1969.(n)

programme.title: Philomena
programme.desc: A teenager in 1950s Ireland becomes pregnant, and is sent to a home for `fallen women', while her baby is forcibly taken from her and sent to America to be adopted. Fifty years later, she meets a disillusioned political journalist who helps to reunite her with her son. Fact-based drama, starring Judi Dench and Steve Coogan.(n)

programme.title: QI XL
programme.desc: An extended edition of the quiz show, in which question-master Stephen Fry probes the subject of Messing with Your Mind, with Sarah Millican, Tommy Tiernan and Josh Widdicombe competing alongside resident panellist Alan Davies. As usual, points are awarded for the answers the host finds most interesting, regardless of whether or not they are correct.(n)

programme.title: Versailles
programme.desc: King Louis XIV's continued insomnia makes him increasingly volatile, meaning Marchal's loyalty counts for nothing following his failure to prove the worst poisonings were solely the work of his now-dead suspect. Claudine continues to investigate the mystery toxin, while Sophie seeks a solution to her situation - a marriage not just loveless, but cruel. Devout Father Pascal dares to reveal to Louis what Madame de Montespan attempted, but it remains to be seen whose account will be believed.(n)

programme.title: Cabaret
programme.desc: A flighty nightclub singer in 1930s Berlin is drawn into a love triangle with a sensitive would-be English writer and an aristocratic German, as the Nazi party grows in might and the country heads inexorably toward war. Oscar-winning musical directed and choreographed by Bob Fosse, starring Liza Minnelli, Joel Grey, Michael York and Helmut Griem.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: A to Z of TV Gardening
programme.desc: Carol Kirkwood's alphabetical journey through the world of horticulture continues with the letter M. Various BBC gardening presenters are mesmerised by magnolias, marvel at the monkey puzzle tree and meet a marigold enthusiast.(n)

programme.title: The Instant Gardener
programme.desc: Helen Skelton and expert designer Danny Clarke head to Northamptonshire to help create a low-allergen garden for a couple whose young son is affected by severe allergies.(n)

programme.title: Gardeners' World
programme.desc: Mark Lane is in Hackney, finding out how a car wrecker's yard at the side of a Tudor National Trust property has been transformed into an award-winning garden used by the local community. Carol Klein visits Oxford Botanic garden to view their euphorbia collection and Rachel de Thame visits a garden which has opened to the public every year for 90 years as part of the National Gardens Scheme. Including Weather.(n)

programme.title: The Beechgrove Garden
programme.desc: Carole Baxter has advice on caring for house plants, and joins Jim McColl and George Anderson in the garden to try to rescue some pot-pound camelias. Jim pays a second visit to the inspirational Firpark School in Motherwell, where children with additional needs learn about horticulture, and Carole is at a cottage-style garden near Huntly, Aberdeenshire.(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Matt Baker reports on a plan to preserve the Suffolk Broads and its wildlife with a vast land purchase, while Ellie Harrison visits a community-run farm where all waste is re-used. John Craven celebrates National Mills Weekend at Bardwell, Tom Heap investigates egg thieves who are endangering rare birds, and Adam Henson and Charlotte Smith meet a young farmer nominated for special recognition by viewers.(n)

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen Best Bites
programme.desc: Matt Tebbutt presents highlights of the series, recalling his favourite moments from previous years in the kitchen.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The North West chefs go all out to impress with their main courses, as they compete for a chance to cook at the Taste of Summer banquet. Paul Askew creates a dish based on his mother's favourite food, Ellis Barrie offers up an imaginative course inspired by former Wimbledon champion Fred Perry, and Tom Parker presents his take on a traditional summer barbecue.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Chefs Ellis Barrie, Tom Parker and Paul Askew continue the battle to cook at a Taste of Summer banquet celebrating 140 years of the Wimbledon Championships. As each of them prepare their desserts, they will all be out to impress as only two can make it through to tomorrow's North West final.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The two remaining North West chefs compete for a place in the national finals, preparing their entire menus for judges Oliver Peyton, Matthew Fort, Andi Oliver and guest judge Greg Rusedski. Greg, a former British number one tennis player, understands the high standards expected at his sport's Grand Slam contests, in this Wimbledon-themed series.(n)

programme.title: NW200 Highlights
programme.desc: Action from the International North West 200 motorcycle race, which passes through Portrush, Portstewart and Coleraine and is a highlight of the British motor sport calendar.(n)

programme.title: None But the Brave
programme.desc: American servicemen crash-land on a remote Pacific island and discover it is already occupied by a stranded Japanese platoon. Both sides grudgingly agree to suspend hostilities and tend their wounded - but only until radio communication is established and rescue arrives. Second World War adventure, directed by and starring Frank Sinatra, with Clint Walker, Tommy Sands, Brad Dexter, Tony Bill, Tatsuya Mihashi and Takeshi Kato.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.sub-title: Galapagos - Islands of Change: Natural World.
programme.desc: From enormous tortoises and deep-diving lizards to fish-eating snakes and birds that hunt giant, venomous centipedes, the wildlife of the Galapagos Islands is unique and bizarre. However, the wilderness that inspired Charles Darwin and the theory of evolution is becoming ever-more crowded due to increased migration and tourism. David Attenborough narrates this documentary, which examines how the Pacific archipelago's animals are adapting to their changing circumstances.(n)

programme.title: Final Score
programme.desc: Jason Mohammad presents updates and results from the final day of the Premier League season, with matches including Hull City v Tottenham Hotspur and Liverpool v Middlesbrough.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Antiques experts Mark Stacey and Philip Serrell head to Stockport Town Hall in Greater Manchester to value the collectibles of members of the public, including a pair of charcoal drawings by artist Trevor Grimshaw and some gold European coins. Plus, presenter Paul Martin visits Manchester Art Gallery, where he admires the work of pre-Raphaelite painter Ford Madox Brown.(n)

programme.title: Inside the Factory
programme.sub-title: Inside the Factory: How Our Favourite Foods Are Made: Chocolate.
programme.desc: The exploration of three household staples continues as Gregg Wallace goes inside a chocolate factory in York, which produces a staggering seven million bars every day. He follows the 24-hour journey from bean to bar and meets the people who work round the clock. Cherry Healey helps out on a production line in Derbyshire, where chocolate boxes are still made by hand, and historian Ruth Goodman delves through the archives to find out what it was like working in factories before machines took over.(n)

programme.title: Dragons' Den
programme.desc: Evan Davis presents the business ideas contest, with regular panellists Deborah Meaden, Peter Jones, Sarah Willingham, Touker Suleyman and Nick Jenkins returning to assess the profit-making potential of the contestants' grand plans. Among the entrepreneurial endeavours in this episode are ideas for miniature pencils, oversized beanbags and a machine for cleaning football boots. However, one contestant finds their hopes may be dashed by the revelation that their company is already heavily in debt.(n)

programme.title: Mexico: Earth's Festival of Life
programme.desc: The series concludes by exploring the north of the country, which is dominated by two deserts - the Sonoran and the Chihuahuan. The programme explores the conditions that have shaped this environment, and reveals how animals including prairie dogs, pygmy owls and aplomado falcons have adapted to thrive in these arid conditions. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Dara and Ed's Road to Mandalay
programme.desc: Dara O Briain and Ed Byrne arrive in Myanmar at a time of great political change. After 50 years of military rule, the first elections were held, heralding a new era of democracy. Along the way, the duo take part in a Buddhist Festival of Light, have their fortunes read from chicken bones and try to master the art of `leg rowing'. The last leg of their journey takes them up the historic road to Mandalay - not in fact a road, but a river - and when they reach their final destination, they visit a comedy troupe called the Moustache Brothers, with whom Ed has a personal connection. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: The Homesman
programme.desc: A single woman living in a frontier town is asked by her church to escort three women traumatised by the hardships of their lives to a safe refuge in the East. Along the way, she saves an outlaw's life and persuades him to help her protect her charges on the perilous journey through the wilderness. Western based on the novel by Glendon Swarthout, directed by and starring Tommy Lee Jones, with Hilary Swank, Meryl Streep and Miranda Otto.(n)

programme.title: Love Is All You Need
programme.desc: A Danish woman recovering from treatment for cancer and the abrupt end of her marriage goes to Italy to attend her daughter's wedding. The trip leads to her meeting the groom's father, a lonely widower, and a relationship develops that helps both to move on from their past troubles. Romantic drama, starring Pierce Brosnan and Trine Dyrholm.(n)

programme.title: Saints and Sinners: Britain's Millennium of Monasteries
programme.desc: Dr Janina Ramirez discovers how monasteries shaped every aspect of medieval Britain and created a dazzling array of art, architecture and literature. She begins her journey on the desolate rock of Skellig Michael, off Ireland's east coast, which is home to the oldest surviving monastery in the British Isles. She investigates the lives led by the early monks and charts the arrival of hermetic Irish monasticism in Anglo-Saxon Northumberland, revealing why monasteries in places such as Lindisfarne and Whitby became beacons of civilisation and literature.(n)

programme.title: Masters of the Pacific Coast: The Tribes of The American Northwest
programme.desc: Part two of two. Archaeologist Dr Jago Cooper reveals how the American Northwest cultural tradition managed to survive against the odds. After European contact, indigenous people of what is now southwest Alaska, British Colombia and Washington State suffered disease, theft and oppression, and Cooper argues that Northwest Coast culture has an extraordinary resilience.(n)

programme.title: Hinterland
programme.desc: DCI Mathias and DI Rhys investigate a local man named Llew Morris, who has been identified as the chief suspect following a fatal shooting at a remote petrol station. The pair decide to visit the house he grew up in, and make a gruesome discovery which seems to cement his guilt. In English and Welsh.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1983
programme.desc: Mike Read and Tommy Vance with music from December 8, with Thompson Twins, Billy Joel, Paul Young, Tina Turner, Tears for Fears, Howard Jones, Culture Club and the Flying Pickets.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1983
programme.desc: Another edition of the long-running music show, hosted by Simon Bates and Janice Long. First aired December 15, 1983.(n)

programme.title: Easy Listening Hits at the BBC
programme.desc: Archive performances by some of the best-known easy-listening musicians of the 1960s and 70s, including Sergio Mendes & Brasil 66, Burt Bacharach, the Carpenters and Andy Williams.(n)

programme.title: Glen Campbell: The Rhinestone Cowboy
programme.desc: An insight into the life of country music star Glen Campbell, documenting his remarkable journey from an impoverished childhood to worldwide fame and success as a guitarist and singer with records including Wichita Lineman and Rhinestone Cowboy. Featuring contributions by family, friends and colleagues including Jimmy Webb, Micky Dolenz and Bob Harris.(n)

programme.title: An Evening with Glen Campbell
programme.desc: An archive concert by country music singer Glen Campbell in which he is accompanied by 80 musicians who played original arrangements of his greatest songs. Performed at London's Royal Festival Hall in 1977.(n)

programme.title: Easy Listening Hits at the BBC
programme.desc: Archive performances by some of the best-known easy-listening musicians of the 1960s and 70s, including Sergio Mendes & Brasil 66, Burt Bacharach, the Carpenters and Andy Williams.(n)

programme.title: The Birth of British Music
programme.desc: Charles Hazlewood turns his attention to Felix Mendelssohn, a German concert hall prodigy who came to London in 1829 aged 20. He reveals how the composer's overture to A Midsummer Night's Dream appealed to the Victorians' fondness for Shakespeare and fairy stories, and takes a stormy journey to Staffa in the Inner Hebrides - the inspiration behind the overture Fingal's Cave. Featuring a performance of Mendelssohn's Elijah from Birmingham Town Hall, with the BBC Concert Orchestra and soloist Andrew Shore. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Timeshift
programme.sub-title: Timeshift: The Last Days of Steam.
programme.desc: Between 1948 and 1960, governments around the world invested in electric tracks and diesel, but in Britain hundreds of steam-powered trains were built. This film looks at the reasons behind their continued production, and asks what happened to them.(n)

programme.title: Tutankhamun: The Truth Uncovered
programme.desc: What killed Tutankhamun? Ever since the tomb of the boy king was discovered in 1922, he has become arguably the most famous pharaoh of all ancient Egypt. But his mysterious death at just 19 years of age has never been explained. Now, Dallas Campbell reveals new scientific research aimed at getting to the truth. A CT scan of the pharaoh's mummified body creates a full-size image of the real Tutankhamun, while DNA analysis uncovers a shocking secret about his family background - and the genetic trail leads to a revolutionary new theory about his sudden and unexpected death.(n)

programme.title: Arena
programme.sub-title: Arena: American Epic: The Big Bang.
programme.desc: The first of three programmes exploring roots music in the US, beginning with the birth of country music and urban blues in the 1920s. As record sales rose in the early days of radio, companies began exploring rural areas in search of new artists. The programme features early recordings by Appalachian country music pioneers the Carter Family and Will Shade and The Memphis Jug Band, whose music prefigured modern rap and RnB. Narrated by Robert Redford.(n)

programme.title: Country at the BBC
programme.desc: A compilation of BBC session performances by country artists from the past four decades, including Tammy Wynette, Emmylou Harris, Johnny Cash, Dolly Parton, Charley Pride, Kris Kristofferson, Garth Brooks, Willie Nelson, Alison Krauss, Taylor Swift, kd lang and Billie Jo Spears.(n)

programme.title: Scottish Football Extra
programme.desc: Darrell Currie is joined by an expert panel at the Falkirk Stadium to discuss the hot topics in Scottish football and look ahead to this weekend's action.(n)

programme.title: Ladbrokes Championship
programme.desc: Falkirk and Dundee United clash in the second leg of the Ladbrokes Championship play-off semi-finals at the Falkirk Stadium.(n)

programme.title: World's Strongest Man
programme.desc: Highlights from The Grand Final of the World's Strongest Man 2016. Ten of the planet's most powerful individuals will battle it out for victory.(n)

programme.title: BT Sport Reload
programme.desc: The best bits from BT Sport over the last week, including Europe's finest goals. Plus, action from the UFC, NBA Playoffs, WTA Tour and the top Challenge and Champions Cup tries.(n)

programme.title: Mobil 1: The Grid
programme.desc: This week's episode features a preview of the upcoming Indy 500, a look at Red Bull's 2011 champion car, the RB7, and meets NASCAR's favourite son, Dale Earnhardt Jr.(n)

programme.title: No Filter Boxing
programme.desc: BT Sport's new countdown show follows Gervonta Davis, Liam Walsh, Daniel Dubois and Anthony Yarde as they prepare for Saturday's BT Sport Fight Night at London's Copperbox Arena.(n)

programme.title: World Rally Championship
programme.desc: Day one highlights from Rally Portugal, the sixth round of the FIA World Rally Championship. Hyundai's Thierry Neuville won the previous two rounds in France and Argentina.(n)

programme.title: Premier League Review
programme.desc: A round-up of the midweek games, including Arsenal v Sunderland, Manchester City v West Brom, Southampton v Manchester United and Leicester City v Tottenham Hotspur.(n)

programme.title: Rugby Tonight

But time is running out for Neville as the legions of infected watch his every move from the safety of the shadows, waiting for the perfect moment to strike. They, too, long to learn the secret that lurks in Neville's blood, though they will have to take caution while attempting to procure it because Neville will sooner die attempting to slay every last one of them than willingly giving up a single drop. programme.title: Ganges
programme.desc: Exploring the story of the river, following its course from the Himalayas to their foothills. The programme reveals its enormous influence on the day-to-day living of a continent, how it has shaped Indian culture and religion and why it attracts a vast array of wildlife including snow leopards, Asiatic brown bears and bearded vultures.(n)

programme.title: Ganges
programme.desc: How the Gangetic Plains, once a wilderness teeming with wildlife, have been transformed into one of the most densely populated places on Earth - and how the region's tigers, lions, cheetahs and other species have been affected by human encroachment on their habitat.(n)

programme.title: Ganges
programme.desc: The final leg of the river's journey sees it join its tributary the Brahmaputra. As the waters merge, they overspill their banks to fan out into hundreds of smaller rivulets and create the world's largest delta. The programme reveals how people and wildlife survive the inhospitable habitat, perhaps the last place on Earth where the Bengal tiger is still king.(n)

programme.title: The Hidden River
programme.desc: A team of explorers sets out to uncover the many secrets hidden along the estimated 1,000km length of the Essequibo, one of the largest rivers in South America. The river rises in Guyana's Acari Mountains, near the Brazilian border, and flows through impenetrable jungles and treacherous swamps before finally reaching the Atlantic Ocean.(n)

programme.title: The Hidden River
programme.desc: Explorers uncover secrets of the Essequibo, the South American river that flows approximately 1,000km from Guyana's Acari Mountains to the Atlantic Ocean.(n)

programme.title: The Hidden River
programme.desc: The final journey down the Essequibo River proves the most challenging as the team try to find its mysterious source.(n)

programme.desc: David Attenborough investigates the opportunities tides create for marine life, showing giant stingrays gliding on currents for a rest, South African sea snails surfing the waves in pursuit of a meal, crabs playing football on a beach, and bottlenose dolphins embarking on a dangerous game of catch. programme.title: Natural World
programme.sub-title: Lobo: The Wolf That Changed America.
programme.desc: Revealing why Ernest Thompson Seton's book about his experiences in 1893, when he set out to kill a wolf that was slaughtering cattle, became the first to portray the animals in a positive light. His account inspired naturalists and changed the way many Americans saw their wilderness. David Attenborough narrates.(n)

programme.title: Mountain Lions: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: The trials and tribulations of two mountain lion families as they raise their kittens in the spectacular Rocky Mountains in Wyoming. David Attenborough narrates.(n)

programme.desc: The wildlife of the mountain range in Asia, including dancing pheasants, square-faced foxes, Tibetan bears and snow leopards.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.sub-title: Natural World - Echo: The Unforgettable Elephant.
programme.desc: Martyn Colbeck and Cynthia Moss examine the legacy of Echo the elephant, who died in 2009 after being followed on film during the final chapter of her life, having guided her family for half a century. With a drought devastating the animals' home in the shadow of Kilimanjaro, a 38-strong band of relatives and descendants must overcome the loss of their leader, hunger and the threat of poachers to survive. Presented by David Attenborough.(n)

programme.title: Clever Monkeys
programme.desc: Documentary examining strikingly human-like behaviour patterns in other primates, discovering examples of simian intelligence in langurs, pygmy marmosets - which `farm' tree sap - and white-faced capuchins who tenderly nurse the victims of battle. David Attenborough narrates.(n)

programme.title: John Ford Goes to War
programme.desc: In this documentary centered on legendary filmmaker John Ford's cinematic contributions to Allied morale during World War II, actor/musician Kris Kristofferson narrates as the How Green Was My Valley director turns his back on Tinseltown in order to fulfill his patriotic duty. By the time the United States became involved in World War II, John Ford was already a film legend, but when Uncle Sam came calling the veteran filmmaker eagerly packed his bags and set his sites on the frontlines. Though Ford did sustain battlefield injuries during the production of the Oscar-winning documentary The Battle of Midway, the remarkable film endeared him to patriotic American audiences across the country and his next wartime effort, 1943's December 7th, proceeded to earn the filmmaker yet another Oscar. In addition to featuring footage from these and other, lesser-known wartime films from Ford, this documentary also offers an intimate look at the complex filmmaker and explores his remarkable legacy through both archive footage and interviews with such notable directors as Oliver Stone and Peter Bogdanovich(n)

programme.title: Space Chimps
programme.desc: In Kirk DeMicco's animated film three supersonic simian spacemen take to the cosmos to find a missing probe, and encounter a whole world of trouble along the way. Ham III, the grandson of the first ever chimp in space, is a wise-cracking smart aleck who makes a living being fired from a cannon. When the Infinity Space Probe goes missing, Ham joins a mission to find it. He's been recruited as a PR stunt, but his fellow Space Chimps, Luna and Titan, are highly trained experts. programme.desc: Former Saturday Night Live "Weekend Update" co-anchors Tina Fey and Amy Poehler co-star in this baby-fever comedy about a single, career-oriented woman who previously put parenthood on hold, and is forced to hire a surrogate mother when she discovers there is only a one-in-a-million chance that she will be able to get pregnant. Kate Holbrook (Fey) is a 37-year-old business executive who has always put her professional life before her personal life, but these days her biological clock is ticking louder than ever before. As with everything else she has accomplished in life, Kate is determined to have a child on her own terms. Unfortunately for Kate, the chance of her ever becoming pregnant is slim to none. Undaunted, a willful Kate drafts South Philly working-class girl Angie Ostrowiski (Poehler) -- a woman who may just be her polar opposite -- to be a surrogate mother. Subsequently informed by the head of the surrogacy center (Sigourney Weaver) that her surrogate is indeed pregnant, the excited mother-to-be soon purchases every child-rearing book she can find and excitedly begins the nesting process. But life hasn't quit throwing Kate curveballs just yet, because when a pregnant Angie shows up on her doorstep with no place to live, the woman who once thrived on order finds her life descending into chaos. Now, as Kate attempts to transform Angie into the ideal expectant mother, this odd couple will discover that families aren't always biological, but occasionally formed through friendship as well. Writer Michael McCullers, who authored the screenplays for Austin Powers: The Spy Who Shagged Me and Undercover Brother in addition to working on Saturday Night Live, makes his feature directorial debut with a self-penned screenplay(n)

Arthur is a high-school student from a dysfunctional family, and does everything in his power to avoid hanging around the house while mom and dad quarrel. When he's not practicing his trombone and performing with the high-school marching band, Arthur can usually be found bussing tables at the local Chinese restaurant and flirting with older waitress Annie. Annie used to be Arthur's babysitter, and is currently struggling to separate from her former high-school sweetheart, Glenn. But being a single mother isn't easy, especially since the troubled Glenn wants nothing more than to clean up his act and reunite his family. Back at school, Arthur and pretty classmate Lila (Olivia Thirlby) have been bonding over their mutual love for all things geeky. Though the casual friendship shows promise of evolving into something more when Lila expresses her true feelings for Arthur, he can't help but becoming distracted by his chaotic family life: his father is moving out of the family home, and his mother is doing everything in her power to maintain some semblance of normalcy. Realizing that happiness is fleeting as his family becomes shattered and Annie experiences a series of distressing encounters with Glenn, Arthur gradually begins to fall for Lisa despite his growing cynicism concerning long-term relationships. Later, on a cold winter morning, Glenn and Annie's past catches up with them in a blinding flash, and the lives of everyone they know are suddenly and irrevocably changed(n)

Taped on the network's Saturday Night Live set in New York, the series did its best to eschew the usual couch-and-desk talk show format; with no monologue and no sketches, Daly simply sat down and talked to his guests, who returned the compliment by avoiding the standard relentless plugging of their latest movie, CD, or TV special. Comedy directed by Ben Stiller, starring Jim Carrey, Matthew Broderick and George Segal.(n)

programme.desc: A single woman begins a new year with resolutions to find love, quit her bad habits and take a step up the career ladder. Her plans crumble as she tries to deal with her mother's infidelity, get over a passionate fling with her boss and come to terms with her feelings for an uptight lawyer. Romantic comedy based on Helen Fielding's novel, starring Renee Zellweger, Hugh Grant and Colin Firth.(n)

Comedy, starring Ben Stiller, Owen Wilson, Will Ferrell, Milla Jovovich, Christine Taylor and David Duchovny.(n)

Romantic comedy, with Sandra Bullock, Bradley Cooper and Thomas Haden Church.(n)

Comedy, starring Tom Green as the tale's narrator, with Breckin Meyer, Seann William Scott, Amy Smart, Paulo Costanzo and DJ Qualls.(n)

When he helps a girl deal with an unpleasant drugs-related experience, he falls madly in love with her - but she only has eyes for a professor. Comedy, starring Jason Biggs, Mena Suvari, Greg Kinnear, Zak Orth, Thomas Sadoski and Dan Aykroyd.(n)

programme.desc: A psychiatrist takes on a friend's client, who turns out to be a well-meaning but annoying neurotic barely able to leave his home. The patient is hugely impressed by the consultant's methods, leading him to follow the therapist on holiday, where he unwittingly proceeds to make his life hell while winning over his family. Comedy, starring Bill Murray, Richard Dreyfuss, Julie Hagerty and Charlie Korsmo.(n)

programme.title: Back to the Future
programme.desc: Teenager Marty McFly travels back to the 1950s in a time machine built by his eccentric inventor friend. The return journey proves tricky enough, but he also accidentally alters the sequence of events that led to his parents falling in love - and has to persuade his future dad to win his mother's heart, or he will never be born. Sci-fi comedy adventure, starring Michael J Fox, Christopher Lloyd, Lea Thompson and Crispin Glover.(n)

programme.title: Back to the Future Part II
programme.desc: Time-travelling teenager Marty McFly travels to the 21st century, where he has to save his children from a terrible fate. However, this proves to have unforeseen consequences when the future version of arch enemy Biff sees a chance to rewrite history for his own benefit, leaving Marty stuck in a twisted parallel universe. Sci-fi comedy sequel, starring Michael J Fox and Christopher Lloyd.(n)

programme.title: Back to the Future Part III
programme.desc: Time-travelling teenager Marty McFly is transported back to the days of the Wild West, where he strives to save his eccentric scientist friend Doc Brown from death at the hands of a villainous gunslinger. Final instalment in the sci-fi comedy trilogy, starring Michael J Fox, Christopher Lloyd, Mary Steenburgen and Thomas F Wilson.(n)

programme.desc: When a series of supernatural disturbances occur in New York city, a quartet of investigators and their dim assistant investigate. Reboot of the 1980s comedy franchise, starring Kristen Wiig, Melissa McCarthy, Kate McKinnon, Leslie Jones and Chris Hemsworth.(n)

programme.desc: A journalist lives her life by her father's maxim that monogamy never works, and has spent her adult life enjoying freedom from commitment. When she is sent to interview a doctor, an attraction develops between them, and she begins to wonder if there mighty be something to be said for a stable relationship. Comedy, starring Amy Schumer, Bill Hader, Brie Larson and Tilda Swinton.(n)

The Simpsons manage to escape and plan to start a new life in Alaska - but learn Springfield is about to be destroyed, and return to save their friends. With the voices of Dan Castellaneta, Julie Kavner, Nancy Cartwright and Yeardley Smith.(n)

Unfortunately, there is one condition - he must somehow find a way to spend $30million in just one month, or he will lose the lot. Meanwhile, two scheming lawyers, who stand to get the money if he fails, are determined to sabotage his efforts. Comedy, starring Richard Pryor, John Candy, Lonette McKee and Jerry Orbach.(n)

He must also fight to defend his animal friends from a big-game hunter. Disney animated adventure, with the voices of Tony Goldwyn and Minnie Driver.(n)

programme.desc: Animation following the further adventures of the little alien, as a host of his fellow experimental creatures arrive on Earth. However, their chaotic efforts to make themselves at home are threatened by the evil Captain Gantu, who is hot on their heels and determined to capture them. With the voices of Chris Sanders, Daveigh Chase, Ving Rhames and David Ogden Stiers.(n)

programme.desc: Clownfish Nemo becomes separated from his friends on the Great Barrier Reef - but the thrill of being able to swim freely and away from his overprotective father turns to horror when he is netted by a diver. His distraught dad sets out on a mission to find him, while the youngster finds himself in a dentist's tropical tank. Pixar animated adventure, with the voices of Albert Brooks, Ellen DeGeneres, Alexander Gould, Willem Dafoe, Barry Humphries and Geoffrey Rush.(n)

programme.title: Finding Dory
programme.desc: Nemo and dad Marlin set out on an underwater adventure to help their forgetful friend Dory find her parents. Animated sequel, with the voices of Ellen DeGeneres, Albert Brooks and Ed O'Neill.(n)

programme.desc: A pet cocker spaniel fears her owners will reject her when they become parents, and the arrival of two villainous siamese cats in the house leaves her feeling more unwelcome. Driven from her home, she encounters a roguish stray mongrel, who introduces her to his carefree life on the streets. Disney animated adventure, with the voices of Barbara Luddy, Larry Roberts and Peggy Lee.(n)

programme.title: The Jungle Book
programme.desc: A boy is raised by animals in the jungle, leading a carefree life with his friends, a laidback bear and a wise panther. The return of a ferocious tiger who hates humans places the youngster's life in danger, and his friends must persuade him to return to the safety of his own people. Disney animated adventure based on Rudyard Kipling's stories, with the voices of Phil Harris and George Sanders.(n)

programme.desc: A rat finds his love of fine food has made him an outcast to his less discerning family. Pixar animated comedy from the director of The Incredibles, with the voices of Patton Oswalt, Ian Holm, Lou Romano and Peter O'Toole.(n)

programme.desc: An intrepid treasure-hunter follows a series of ingenious clues in a perilous quest to track down a war chest hidden by America's founding fathers generations before. He has to contend with determined rivals in the shape of a treacherous associate and the FBI. Action adventure, starring Nicolas Cage, Diane Kruger, Sean Bean and Justin Bartha.(n)

programme.title: The Hunchback of Notre Dame
programme.desc: A deformed bell-ringer living reclusively in a cathedral in the heart of medieval Paris is tempted out of seclusion when a gypsy festival arrives and captures his imagination. Here in the outside world, he learns the cruel government minister who raised him is hatching a plan to wipe out the gypsies, so he resolves to protect his new friends. Disney animation, with the voices of Tom Hulce, Demi Moore and Kevin Kline.(n)

Thriller, starring Bette Davis, Carroll Baker, David McCallum and Lynn-Holly Johnson.(n)

programme.title: Willow Creek
programme.desc: A young couple (Alexie Gilmore, Bryce Johnson) venture into Six Rivers National Forest in Northern California to search for Bigfoot, and make a terrifying discovery in this found-footage horror film from writer-director Bobcat Goldthwait. Convinced that he will capture video evidence of Sasquatch at the same place where the legendary Patterson-Gimlin film was shot, Jim (Bryce Johnson) persuades his skeptical girlfriend Kelly (Alexie Gilmore) to join him on a cryptozoological excursion into the deep woods. Before Jim and Kelly set out on their mission, however, they first visit Willow Creek -- a town that thrives on the Bigfoot phenomenon -- to interview the locals about the legend. There, the couple are repeatedly warned that the forest can be a dangerous place at night -- warnings that go unheeded by Jim as he single-mindedly focuses on making the journey he's dreamt about for years. Later, in the darkened woods, however, the once-carefree couple experience paralyzing fear when someone -- or something -- begins rooting around their campsite, and uttering inhuman howls. Uncertain if they've actually survived an encounter with Bigfoot or simply fallen victim to a cruel prank by the locals, Jim and Kelly agree to pack their bags, and return to civilization at sunrise. But this is just the beginning of a nightmare that neither of them may ever awaken from(n)

programme.desc: The world's most inept detective returns to the screen in this modern slapstick comedy. France's come-from-behind victory in the World Cup soccer championships turns tragic when the team's coach, Yves Gulant (Jason Statham), is murdered during a post-game celebration. The media and the public demand that the killer be found out and brought to justice, and Chief Inspector Dreyfus (Kevin Kline) of the Paris Police pledges to put his best man on the case. Then one night, after breaking up a fight in the club, Ali meets the radiant Stephanie (Marion Cotillard), and slips her his number after dropping her off safely at home. Though Stephanie's position on the high end of the social spectrum makes romance an unlikely prospect for the pair, a tragic accident at Marineland robs her of her legs, and finds her reaching out in desperation to Ali. Her spirit broken by the same tragedy that took her legs, Stephanie gradually finds the courage to go on living trough transcendent moments spent with Ali -- a man with precious little pity, but an enormous love of life(n)

programme.desc: A girl plays Cupid for her mom, but has to invent the right man to woo her in this romantic comedy. Jean Hamilton (Heather Locklear) is a single mother with two daughters, teenaged Holly (Hilary Duff) and grade-school-aged Zoe (Aria Wallace). Fortysomething Jean has stumbled in and out of a number of bad relationships in her lifetime, and is desperate to find a good man; however, Holly has grown a bit tired of Jean's favored means of therapy after a bad breakup -- packing up the family and moving to a new city.
